1½ cups graham cracker crumbs (180g, from 11 large graham cracker sheets)
▢3 tablespoons light brown sugar
▢6 tablespoons unsalted butter melted (85g)

# Cheesecake Bars

### Ingredients

| Quantity | Ingredient |
| -------- | ---------- |
| 180g | cookie crumbs |
| 3 tbsp | light brown sugar |
| 85g | butter, melted |
| 226g | cream cheese, room tempearature |
| 133g | sugar |
| 80g | sour cream, room temperature |
| 2 tsp | lemon juice |
| 1 tsp | vanilla extract | 
| 3 | eggs, room temperature

### Instructions
8x8 in pan

### Instructions

* Heat oven to 350F.
* In a 8x8 pan:
  * Line pan with parchment paper.
  * Combine `cookie crumbs`, `brown sugar`, `melted butter`.
  * Place cookie mixture in baking pan.
  * Press firmly.
  * Bake for 10-12 minutes until golden around edges.
* Decrease oven to 325F.
* In a Large Bowl:
  * Beat `cream cheese` for 1 minute.
  * Add `sugar`. Beat for 1 minute.
  * Add `sour cream`, `lemon juice`, `vanilla`. Beat for 1 minute.
  * Add `eggs`. Beat on slow for 30 seconds or until combined.
* Pour the mixture onto the crust
* Bake for 30-35 minutes until edges are puffy.
* Cool on wire rack for 2 hours.
* Refrigerate for 4 hours.
